24/10/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- US Ambassador to Bulgaria James Pardew confirmed Saturday (23 October) that the US government has imposed sanctions on two Bulgarian firms -- Beta JSC and KAS Engineering Consortium/BMG-M -- for trading with countries that "back terrorism". The companies will be deprived of access to US government contracts for one year, and will be denied licences for imports of military equipment in the United States. (bTV, Sega - 23/10/04; Mediapool - 22/10/04)
